The paper deals with interference management in a network, which is a topic covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of blockchain technology and monetary mechanisms falls under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses security and incentives, which are topics covered in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with cooperative transmission and resource sharing, which are topics covered in the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
